<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000046125"><TermName>peritoneal cavity</TermName><TermPronunciation>(PAYR-ih-toh-NEE-ul KA-vuh-tee)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>The space within the abdomen that contains the intestines, the stomach, and the liver. It is bound by thin membranes.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000707712" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;peritoneal cavity&quot;" language="en" id="_3"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000707713" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;cavidad peritoneal&quot;" language="es" id="_4"/><SpanishTermName>cavidad peritoneal</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Espacio dentro del abdomen que contiene los intestinos, el estómago y el hígado. Está ligado por membranas delgadas.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition></GlossaryTerm>
